<br>
<br>
Hello, magician community, <br>
<br>
I’m staying anonymous for <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>several</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> reasons: I do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> wish to be flamed, or to have my guild looked at  from a hostile point of view because of the things I will say below. I do not wish to attract negative attention to my friends, my guild or myself, but I do want to share <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  my</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>personal</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> experiences in the end game as it stands. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Vex Thal</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: <br>
<br>
I log on nearly every night and enter Vex Thal.  My routine is to offer coldstones to the blind, focus items for those that lack them and to make mod rods for all that asked.  Pre-raid, I’m contributing to the overall success of my guild by taking care of loose ends. Recently, safe-points for CoTH points have been altered, and we’ve been fighting our way back in, which is a slow and tedious process, especially after having cleared the zone a month prior. <br>
<br>
We clear the hallways in Vex Thal, often times we get 2-4 shades or four-arms that we clear to advance forward.  My guild has less than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  4</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> active magi, often times it’s just me with another person who bots a mage. <br>
<br>
Here is where my scenario differs from 90% of what I see on this board, especially from recent posters that claim their guild has <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  no</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->[/b] use for them other than <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  mod rods</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  I use my epic pet, along with muzzle, burnout 4 and velocity – I keep him by me at all times. I help our two shamans with malosini, and if they have their hands full, I mala and then malosini.  I damage shield my group often now, especially since the stacking issue with rangers have been fixed.   Most of the time I’m with a shaman, and even though the Shield of Auras is quite nice, it’s not as powerful as mod rodding with quick summoning 3 from 4k hp while being topor’d.  I drop a few rods and watch to see how quickly they get picked up – if they’re on the ground for more than 30 seconds, I do other things – mainly nuke or rain the crap out of stuff, rod down more, repeat if I desire. It’s common for my group to get experience.  <br>
<br>
If there’s a bad pull, and a monk is FD’d with 4-5 reds / yellows on him, I can summon him back to us in 6 seconds, this ability has saved my guild time, money and energy. If a wizard falls in lava, I can get him too.  Couple people log in late?  No problem, pair me with a druid wizard, or even a necro and I’ll get ‘em here in less than a minute.<br>
<br>
When it comes down to an engagement with a named boss, clerics will need mana, there’s no way around it. Some Luclin encounters take more than half an hour, and even with AE bard song, and necros twitching, clerics tap dry all too often.  Because my cast time is faster, I can make rods faster and more efficiently. I can drop theoretically twice as many rods in the same time as a mage without his summoned focus ring, or any form of quick summoning – that gives me more time to do the other things, which I described above.  On most encounters, or bosses, that we’re come across, I’m fully able to use my pet as I see fit.  <br>
<br>
While a Kunark based weapon wont be as powerful as a Luclin weapon in a raiding zone like Ssra Temple, my pet still contributes a lot – DPS is still DPS.  Add in my nukes, my helping debuff, my mana rods and damage shields and you have a pleasant picture forming. <br>
<br>
I reek power from my veins. There is no other class in the game that can contribute to a raid like I can.  I’m the oil that helps the gears move, which drives the engine. You want focus items – you got `em.   15% save on mana per nuke for the wizards, same deal with the casting ring for clerics – nothing short of a lifesaver in a clutch situation.  My mana rods help others stay near FM, and because I gauge how quickly they get used in clearing, I’m able to nuke to my hearts content and rod down with a shaman.  Sure, my nukes are not as big, or flashy as a Wizards – but, I find myself nuking more than they do in some situations.  Still envious of  “manaburn”?  It makes a little dent on the yard trash in VT.  Dire charm?  Nope, can’t use it here.  5k nukes with GGS does impress me, but seeing a wizard summoned and killed because he mistimed his nukes makes me laugh – hard.<br>
<br>
I’ve never really needed to see pet parses to know I’m doing damage, in exp groups or raids.  I know I contribute more than my fair share, so do my friends and guild mates – they take the utter best care of me.  In my months of being with them, I’ve never been called a rod whore, coth slut, or anything in between.  My guild knows I’m good for more than just rods, and I’m nothing short of honored to raid with them in the way mages should raid:  With pets, nukes and summon spells up paired with an eager attitude that is almost extinct from the mage class on my server, I give it my all by making full use of my class and I’m nothing short of happy with my performance as it stands. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  In conclusion</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>strongly</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> believe mages are raid balanced in Luclin.  We bring a beautiful mix of damage and utility that guilds could not go without.  Our epic is on par with Knight classes that use primal – not an end game weapon, but still incredibly good to use.<br>
I’m a major force in exp groups.  I bring powerful abilities that could be separated to two classes – or more.  I’m not worried about getting groups, if a warrior or cleric at my level don’t understand how powerful my class is, I don’t want to group with them – simple as that.   <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  I love our class.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Signed, <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Anonymous <br>
Of the Anonymous server <br>
Proud member of an Anonymous VT capable guild. </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
